{"lemma": "رُكْبَةٌ", "slug": "رُكْبَةٌ", "root": "ر.ك.ب", "root_slug": "ر-ك-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ر-ك-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n16460"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "knee", "fa": "زانو", "ur": "گھٹنا", "tr": "diz", "id": "lutut", "bn": "হাঁটু", "es": "rodilla", "fr": "genou", "de": "Knie", "ru": "колено", "zh": "膝盖"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "knee"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plural of رَاكِب (rākib)", "tags": ["form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Perhaps from Proto-Semitic *rukba- (“knee”), metathetic form of Proto-Semitic *birk- (“knee”)."}, "ipa": ["/ruk.ba/", "/ra.ka.ba/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n16460", "headword_ar": "رُكْبَةٌ", "root": "rkb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "a word of well-known meaning, (S, Msb,) [The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "knee;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e., in a man,] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "joint between the lower parts of the thigh and the upper parts of the shank:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, K:) or [in a quadruped,] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "joint between the metacarpus and the radius"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoSilu AlwaZiyfi waAl*~iraAEi", "text_ar": "مَوْصِلُ الوَظِيفِ وَالذِّرَاعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): this is the right explanation: in the K,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoDiE", "text_ar": "مَوْضِع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is erroneously put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoSil", "text_ar": "مَوْصِل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": [this explanation is evidently given accord. to the terms employed in the anatomy of quadrupeds as compared to human beings: in that which next follows, there is certainly an omission, which I have endeavoured to supply:] or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobataAni", "text_ar": "رُكْبَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the fore legs of the camel are the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "two joints that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "project forwards, in like manner as do, in the hind legs, those that"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are next the belly"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the stifle-joints"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when he lies down upon his breast with folded legs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the two joints that project behind [in the hind legs, namely, the hocks,] are called the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuroquwbaAni", "text_ar": "عُرْقُوبَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": in every quadruped, the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rkbtAn", "text_ar": "ركبتان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are in the fore legs, and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ErqwbAn", "text_ar": "عرقوبان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are in the hind legs: and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Erqwb", "text_ar": "عرقوب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is what is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoSilu AlwaZiyfi", "text_ar": "مَوْصِلُ الوَظِيفِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. the upper joint of the metatarsus]: (TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rkbp", "text_ar": "ركبة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mirofaq", "text_ar": "مِرْفَق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which in a man is the elbow, but here seems to mean the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lower joint"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iraAE", "text_ar": "ذِرَاع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "radius"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] of anything [i. e. of any beast]: (K:) [from its being said in the S and Msb that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobap", "text_ar": "رُكْبَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is “ well known, ” I conclude that there is no real discrepancy in the foregoing explanations: it is perhaps needless to add that the term"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobap", "text_ar": "رُكْبَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is now universally applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "knee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a man and to what we commonly call the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "knee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a horse and the like:] the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukabN", "text_ar": "رُكَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) i. e. the pl. of mult., and the pl. of pauc. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobaAtN", "text_ar": "رُكْبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukabaAtN", "text_ar": "رُكَبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukubaAtN", "text_ar": "رُكُبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) Lh mentions the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baEiyrN musotawoqiHu Alr~ukabi", "text_ar": "بَعِيرٌ مُسْتَوْقِحُ الرُّكَبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A hardkneed camel"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as though the term"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rukobapN", "text_ar": "رُكْبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "were applied to each part, and the pl. used accord. to this application. (TA.) ―         -b2-  One says [of an agitating affair or event],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^amorN A@SoTak~ato fiyhi Alr~ukabu waHak~ato", "text_ar": "اَمْرٌ ا@صْطَكَّتْ فِيهِ الرُّكَبُ وَحَكَّتْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhi Alr~ukobapu Alr~ukabapa", "text_ar": "فِيهِ الرُّكْبَةُ الرُّكَبَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An affair,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "event, in which the knees knocked together, and in which the knee rubbed the knee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b3-  And of one who has the mark of prostration in prayer on his forehead, between his eyes, (L,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayona Eayonayohi mivolu rukobapi AlEanozi", "text_ar": "بَيْنَ عَيْنَيْهِ مِثْلُ رُكْبَةِ العَنْزِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Between his eyes is the like of the knee of the she-goat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A, * L.) And of any two things that are alike, or correspondent,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "humaA karukobataY AlEanozi", "text_ar": "هُمَا كَرُكْبَتَى العَنْزِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They are like the two knees of the she-goat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; because her two knees fall together upon the ground when she lies down. (L.) ―         -b4-  And it is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ar~u", "text_ar": "شَرُّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aAsi mano miloHuhu EalaY rukEbatihi", "text_ar": "النَّاسِ مَنْ مِلْحُهُ عَلَى رُكعبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The worst of men is he whose fat is upon his knee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: applied to him who is quickly angered; and to the perfidious: (Meyd, TA:) the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "miloHuhu EalaY rukobatihi", "text_ar": "مِلْحُهُ عَلَى رُكْبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also used as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The smallest thing makes him angry:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) and a poet says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "laA talumohaA A_in~ahaA mino EuSobapK\n                      \n                     \n                        miloHuhaA mawoDuwEapN fawoqa Alr~ukabo"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Blame her not; for she is of a set of people whose fat is placed above the knees:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "perhaps meaning, for she is but a woman; as women are generally fat in the part above the knee]: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino nisowapK", "text_ar": "مِنْ نِسْوَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the place of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino EuSobapK", "text_ar": "مِنْ عُصْبَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of women whose object of anxiety,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "care, is fatness"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fat:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Meyd, TA:) so that the prov. seems to mean that the worst of men is he who has not such intelligence as bids him to do that which is praiseworthy, but only bids him to do that in which is inconstancy and levity, and an inclining to the dispositions of women, to the love of fatness and fat. (Meyd.) [See other explanations in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mlH", "text_ar": "ملح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]       -A2-  Also The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lower part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSol", "text_ar": "اَصْل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the plant"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Sil~iyaAnap", "text_ar": "صِلِّيَانَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when it has been cut."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "A", "K", "TA", "L", "Meyd"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}